## summary se function
summarySE <- function(data=NULL, measurevar, groupvars=NULL, na.rm=FALSE, conf.interval=.95) {
  library(doBy)
  
  # New version of length which can handle NA's: if na.rm==T, don't count them
  length2 <- function (x, na.rm=FALSE) {
    if (na.rm) sum(!is.na(x))
    else       length(x)
  }
  
  # Collapse the data
  formula <- as.formula(paste(measurevar, paste(groupvars, collapse=" + "), sep=" ~ "))
  datac <- summaryBy(formula, data=data, FUN=c(length2,mean,sd), na.rm=na.rm)
  
  # Rename columns
  names(datac)[ names(datac) == paste(measurevar, ".mean",    sep="") ] <- measurevar
  names(datac)[ names(datac) == paste(measurevar, ".sd",      sep="") ] <- "sd"
  names(datac)[ names(datac) == paste(measurevar, ".length2", sep="") ] <- "N"
  
  datac$se <- datac$sd / sqrt(datac$N)  # Calculate standard error of the mean
  
  # Confidence interval multiplier for standard error
  # Calculate t-statistic for confidence interval: 
  # e.g., if conf.interval is .95, use .975 (above/below), and use df=N-1
  ciMult <- qt(conf.interval/2 + .5, datac$N-1)
  datac$ci <- datac$se * ciMult
  
  return(datac)
}

Did some subjects get more answers (and show more curiosity) across items than others?

Calculating difference in significance of correlations between curiosity and prior knowledge

  n = 1
  number_of_samples <- 500
  
  sample_num <- c()
  
  corr_value <- c()
  
  while (n <= number_of_samples) {
    samp <- sample(1:5973, size = 500, replace = TRUE, prob = NULL)
    minidataset <- data[c(samp), ]
    correlation <- cor(minidataset$scale_curiosity, minidataset$sub_scale_sim)
    sample_num <- append(sample_num, n)
    corr_value <- append(corr_value, correlation)
    n = n+1

  } 
  
correlations_cur_subsim <- sort(as.numeric(unlist(corr_value)))



# function to create bootstrapped confidence intervals for cur ~ rater similarity
  n = 1
  number_of_samples <- 500
  
  sample_num <- c()
  
  corr_value <- c()
  
  while (n <= number_of_samples) {
    samp <- sample(1:5973, size = 500, replace = TRUE, prob = NULL)
    minidataset <- data[c(samp), ]
    correlation <- cor(minidataset$scale_curiosity, minidataset$avg_zsim)
    sample_num <- append(sample_num, n)
    corr_value <- append(corr_value, correlation)
    n = n+1

  } 
  
correlations_cur_rsim <- sort(as.numeric(unlist(t(corr_value))))


# function to create bootstrapped confidence intervals for subsim ~ rater similarity
  n = 1
  number_of_samples <- 500
  
  sample_num <- c()
  
  corr_value <- c()
  
  while (n <= number_of_samples) {
    samp <- sample(1:5973, size = 500, replace = TRUE, prob = NULL)
    minidataset <- data[c(samp), ]
    correlation <- cor(minidataset$sub_scale_sim, minidataset$avg_zsim)
    sample_num <- append(sample_num, n)
    corr_value <- append(corr_value, correlation)
    n = n+1

  } 
  
correlations_subsim_rsim <- sort(as.numeric(unlist(t(corr_value))))


lower <- (.1*500)/2
upper <- 500-lower

cor_subsim <- cor(dataframe$scale_curiosity, dataframe$sub_scale_sim)
cor_rsim <- cor(dataframe$scale_curiosity, dataframe$avg_zsim)
cor_both <- cor(dataframe$sub_scale_sim, dataframe$avg_zsim)

names <- c("cur_subsim", "cur_rsim", "subsim_rsim")
lower_ci <- c(correlations_cur_subsim[lower], correlations_cur_rsim[lower], correlations_subsim_rsim[lower])
upper_ci <- c(correlations_cur_subsim[upper], correlations_cur_rsim[upper], correlations_subsim_rsim[lower])
r_value <- c(cor_subsim, cor_rsim, cor_both)

corrs <- data.frame(names, r_value, lower_ci, upper_ci)





corr_r2r3 <- ((corrs$r_value[3] - .5*(corrs$r_value[1]*corrs$r_value[3]))*(1-corrs$r_value[1]^2 - corrs$r_value[2]^2 - corrs$r_value[3]^2) + corrs$r_value[3]^2)/((1-corrs$r_value[1]^2)*(1-corrs$r_value[2]^2))

L <- corrs$r_value[1] - corrs$r_value[2] - sqrt((corrs$r_value[1] - corrs$lower_ci[1])^2 + (corrs$upper_ci[2] - corrs$r_value[2])^2 - 2*(corr_r2r3)*(corrs$r_value[1] - corrs$lower_ci[1])*(corrs$upper_ci[2]-corrs$r_value[2]))

U <- corrs$r_value[1] - corrs$r_value[3] + sqrt((corrs$upper_ci[1]-corrs$r_value[1])^2 + (corrs$r_value[3]-corrs$lower_ci[2])^2 - 2*corr_r2r3*(corrs$upper_ci[1]- corrs$r_value[1])*(corrs$r_value[3]-corrs$lower_ci[2]))

L
## [1] 0.05698051
U
## [1] 0.1968617
